The Catholic diocese of Kitui will on Thursday hold a joint requiem mass for the 10 pupils of St Gabriel Boarding School who died in a road accident on Saturday night. Father Joseph Mwongela in a statement said the requiem mass will be held at St Josephâ€™s Junior Seminary in Mwingi. The Catholic Church is also raising Sh1 million to fund the sendoff of the pupils. The crash happened in Kanginga. The school bus was travelling from Mombasa to Mwingi when it collided with a lorry. The driver lost control of the vehicle and veered off into Kanginga River at 11pm.